  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The retention of a separate bin store area with raised platform and altered railings, by reason of design and visual appearance, fails to respect the established pattern of development along Richmond Avenue and its surrounding local context.  The development forms a discordant feature when viewed from the streetscene and undermines the character and appearance to the front elevation of this locally listed building and its wider setting within the Barnsbury Conservation Area. The proposal is contrary to policies D1 (Overall design), D4(Designing in context)  and D11(Alterations and extensions) of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002, policy 9 of Islingtonâ€™s Draft Core Strategy, Islington Urban Design Guide 2006,conservation guidance note 10  and PPS 5."
